s."Through a genealogical approach, Uneasy Military Encounters addresses broad conceptual questions of imperial politics in a non-Western context: How can we understand imperial policing in a country that was never colonized? How is "Islam" constructed in a state that is officially secular and promotes Buddhist tolerance? What are the (historical) dynamics of imperial patriarchy in a context internationally known for its gender pluralism? The resulting ethnography excavates the imperial politics of concrete encounters between the military and the southern population in the ongoing conflict in southern Thailand.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aBuddhismzThailand, SouthernxRelationsxIslam. 0aCounterinsurgencyzThailand, Southern. 0aEthic conflictzThailand, Southern. 0aEthnic conflictzThailand, Southern. 0aIslamzThailand, SouthernxRelationsxBuddhism. 0aMilitarismzThailand, Southern. 0aRace discriminationzThailand, Southern. 0aSexismzThailand, Southern. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Asian.2bisacsh  aSouthern Thailand, the three southern border provinces, Patani, Counterinsurgency, Imperial Formation, Race, Religion, Gender, Islam.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501751356zCo-access DOI >> click Walter